Together with the [[Xucphra Corporation]], the '''Zaltin Corporation''' produced and marketed [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]] for [[The galaxy/Legends|the entire galaxy]]. The corporation was based on [[Thyferra/Legends|Thyferra]], and along with Xucphra was granted a contract by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] to produce bacta. This contract gave Zaltin and Xucphra a monopoly that came to be known as the [[Bacta Cartel/Legends|Bacta Cartel]].

==History==
Unlike [[Xucphra Corporation|Xucphra]], Zaltin was more sympathetic to both the native [[Vratix/Legends|Vratix]] and the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]], and entered the [[Bacta Cartel/Legends|cartel]] out of necessity. Feeling the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] was doomed and recognizing the Vratix would eventually seek independence through the [[Ashern]] [[Terrorist/Legends|terrorist]] organization, Zaltin sent [[Bror Jace]] (whose family was a primary stockholder in Zaltin) to fly in [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] and began providing covert assistance to them in the form of money and security.

During the [[Bacta War]], Zaltin was outlawed by [[Ysanne Isard]], their members either imprisoned or fleeing into the jungles to join the [[Ashern]]. They provided aid to [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] and his group as they attempted to liberate Thyferra, accepting members of his team into their ranks and sending Jace to join them again. After the war, Zaltin was allowed to produce bacta again, this time for the Vratix.

In some point after [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], [[Derek Klivian/Legends|Derek Klivian]] became spokesman for Zaltin Corporation.

